    "content": "+1 to Scott's domain review. No additional a11y concerns to raise beyond what I have already stated.\n\nOne small connection: Scott's observation about `ContextName::parse()` normalizing the `@` prefix is relevant from a user-facing perspective too. Consistent naming means screen reader users will hear consistent context names across the UI (e.g., always \"@computer\", never sometimes \"computer\" and sometimes \"@computer\"). The parse-don't-validate pattern serves accessibility indirectly by preventing inconsistent data from reaching the templates.\n\nOtherwise, I agree with the emerging consensus: good quality, process improvement needed on commit granularity."
  }
